# Infrastructure Layer Rules

## Core Principle
Infrastructure implements ports ONLY.

- MUST NOT contain business logic
- MUST NOT define domain rules
- MUST NOT be used directly by application layer

---

## Allowed

- Port implementations (adapters)
- NestJS modules (integration only)
- External service clients (Qdrant, Neo4j, Prisma, Redis, S3, Ollama)
- Mappers (domain ↔ persistence)
- Config factory

---

## Forbidden

- Business logic
- Domain entities
- Application services
- Direct usage in handlers
- Cross-layer imports (infrastructure → application/domain logic)

---

## Module-per-service rule

Each external system MUST be isolated:
